article.headline: Bradley 70, Illinois St. 62
article.story: NORMAL, Ill. (AP) -- Zach Andrews scored 15 points while shooting 7-of-8 from the floor to lead Bradley to a 70-62 win over Illinois State on Saturday. The Braves (16-9, 7-6 Missouri Valley) committed just five turnovers for the game while forcing 15 Illinois State turnovers that lead to 21 points. The Redbirds (12-12, 4-9) jumped out to a 10-0 lead to start the game, but Bradley battled back to tie it at 19 with 9:57 left in the first half and led 34-30 at halftime. After trailing throughout the second half, Illinois State rallied to take a 45-43 lead with 12:23 remaining on a jumper by Dominitrix Johnson. But Andrews and Matt Salley answered with layups and Bradley never trailed again. Will Franklin also scored 15 points for the Braves. Danny Adams came off the Bradley bench to score 14 points while shooting 4-for-6 from 3-point range. Johnson scored 14 points off the bench to lead the Redbirds, while Greg Dilligard added 11 points and a game-high 10 rebounds.
